FORMAT: 1A

# Graph

Graph provides RESTful API access to Elgg resources.

# API Root [/]

## Retrieve a list of API resources [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "status": 200,
            "message": "OK",
            "result": [
                {
                    "method": ":site",
                    "call_method": "GET",
                    "endpoint": "GET /:site",
                    "description": "Returns site entity attritubes and basic configuration values"
                },
                {
                    "method": ":site/users",
                    "call_method": "GET",
                    "endpoint": "GET /:site/users",
                    "description": "Returns a list of users registered on the site",
                    "parameters": {
                        "1": {
                            "name": "limit",
                            "description": "Number of entries to return (max 50)",
                            "type": "integer",
                            "default": 10
                        },
                        "2": {
                            "name": "offset",
                            "description": "Offset from the start of the list",
                            "type": "integer"
                        },
                        "3": {
                            "name": "sort",
                            "description": "Sorting order",
                            "type": "array",
                            "default": {
                                "time_created": "DESC"
                            }
                        }
                    }
                },
            ]
        }

+ Response 403 (application/json)

        {
            "result": null,
            "status": 403,
            "message": "You do not have access to the requested endpoint"
        }


## Group Site

Resources related to site entity.

## Site [/{site_uid}]

Resources related to the site entity.
{site_uid} can be replaced with a magic keyword 'site'

### Retrieve site details [GET]

+ Response 200 (application/json)

        {
            "result": {
                "nodes": [
                    {
                        "type": "site",
                        "subtype": "",
                        "uid": "se1",
                        "name": "Site Name",
                        "description": "Site description",
                        "url": "http://example.com/",
                        "email": "admin@example.com",
                        "allow_registration": true,
                        "default_access": "1",
                        "debug": null,
                        "walled_garden": true,
                        "time_created": "2014-11-14T03:46:59-08:00",
                        "enabled": "yes"
                    }
                ]
            },
            "status": 200,
            "message": "OK",
        }

+ Response 403 (application/json)

        {
            "result": null,
            "status": 403,
            "message": "You do not have access to the requested endpoint"
        }

+ Response 404 (application/json)

        {
            "result": null,
            "status": 400,
            "message": "Node with id {site_uid} not found"
        }

## Site Activity [/{site_uid}/activity]

### Retrieve site activity [GET]

Returns a list of latest site activity (river)

+ Parameters

    + fields (string, optional) - comma separated list of fields to return
    + limit (number, optional) - number of activities to list
        + Default: `10`
    + offset (number, optional) - offset from the list start
    + types (array[string], optional) - constrain by entity types
    + subtypes (array[string], optional) - constrain by entity subtypes
    + action_types (array[string], optional) - constrain by action types

